The paper describes an approach for ranking triples using entity links in a large web crawl, which involves techniques related to information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The use of a large collection of web data and the deployment of a search strategy also suggest a connection to databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a baseline approach using Wikipedia abstracts, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
